{"title": "Good Soldier", "description": "The Good Soldier (1915) \"... is set just before World War I and chronicles the tragedies of the lives of two seemingly perfect couples. The novel is told using a series of flashbacks in non-chronological order, a literary technique pioneered by Ford. It also makes use of the device of the unreliable narrator, as the main character gradually reveals a version of events that is quite different from what the introduction leads you to believe. The novel was loosely based on two incidents of adultery and on Ford's messy personal life.\u201d (Summary by Wikipedia)<br /><br />\n\nMusic in sections 1-5 \"Minuet in G flat major and Valse Bluette\" by Beethoven.", "duration": 27575, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "281", "name": "Ford Madox Ford"}], "coverArt": "http://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt5/good_soldier_1007.jpg", "copyright_year": "1915", "genres": ["General Fiction", "War & Military Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Denny Sayers (d. 2015)"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "TriciaG"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "01 - Part 1, Section 1", "readers": [331], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/good_soldier_0912_librivox/goodsoldier_01_ford_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1031}, {"section": 2, "title": "02 - Part 1, Section 2", "readers": [331], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/good_soldier_0912_librivox/goodsoldier_02_ford_64kb.mp3", "duration": 924}, {"section": 3, "title": "03 - Part 1, Section 3", "readers": [331], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/good_soldier_0912_librivox/goodsoldier_03_ford_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1508}, {"section": 4, "title": "04 - Part 1, Section 4", "readers": [331], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/good_soldier_0912_librivox/goodsoldier_04_ford_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1344}, {"section": 5, "title": "05 - Part 1, Sec